<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NATO Chief Strongly Condemns Bosnian Serbs for Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Javier Solana, secretary
general of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization, today condemned
the Bosnian Serbs for their violence directed against the NATO-led
Stabilization Force (SFOR) troops and the international community.
</P>
<P>
He fully supports the steps taken by SFOR troops in cooperation
with other international organizations to ensure appropriate
control of the special police, to support the International Police
Task Force and to prevent the outbreak of hostilities.
</P>
<P>
"The SFOR will not hesitate to take the necessary measures
including the use of force against media networks or programs
inciting attacks on the SFOR or other organizations," said the
NATO chief.
</P>
<P>
Solana reaffirmed that the SFOR will continue to carry out its
mission firmly but fairly and will not tolerate the use of force
or intimidation as a means of resolving political issues.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, hundreds of Bosnian Serbs pelted SFOR troops with
rocks, forcing them to pull out from a police station in Brcko.
</P>
<P>
Brcko townspeople, roused from their sleep by air raid sirens
that wailed for hours, reportedly attacked dozens of American
peacekeeping soldiers, accusing the latter of conducting like the
Nazi occupying force.
</P>
<P>
In another development, local Serb residents at Bijeljina
reportedly blocked the town center to SFOR troops from taking over
the police station and a television transmitter.
</P>
<P>
Tensions rose sharply over the past few days in Bosnian Serb
areas between SFOR troops and local residents loyal to their
wartime leader Radovan Karadzic as his power struggle was fueled
up with Bosnian Serb President Biljana Plavsic.
</P>
<P>
Those backing Plavsic and Karadzic loyalists have been vying
for local television transmitters.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, the European Union also blamed riots in the
Bosnian Serb towns of Brcko and Bijeljina as an insurrection
against the presence of the international community.
</P>
<P>
It said that violent acts against the SFOR and the
International Police Task Force are intolerable.
</P>
<P>
The union said that it would not accept such a provocation and
it urged Bosnian Serbs to refrain from further provocative acts
and to stop propaganda that is of the nature of inciting
insecurity and instability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
