<HEADLINE> Brazilian Luiz Eduardo Lima Wins Men's 400m Freestyle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MESSINA, Sicily, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Luiz Eduardo Lima of Brazil
overtook Hungarian Bela Szabados in the last 15 meters to take the
title of the men's 400 meters freestyle at the Universiade here on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Szabados led all the way till the last 15 meters when he was
exhausted and slowed down to give Lima the lead.
</P>
<P>
Lima was timed 3 minutes 53.91 seconds at the finish. Szabados won
the silver medal at 3:54.30 and Hisato Yasui of Japan was third at
3:55.05. 
</P>
