<HEADLINE> Death Toll in Floods Rises to 91 in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 29 (Xinhua) -- The death toll in floods
caused by heavy monsoon rains in Pakistan has risen to 91, the
official Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) reported this evening.
</P>
<P>
The floods also left 21,000 homeless in Pakistan's eastern
province of Punjab and North West Frontier province in the past
couple of days.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of houses were damaged and more than 36,000 hectares
of farmland were still submerged, the APP said.
</P>
<P>
The government has called in the army to help the affected
people and protect dams.
</P>
<P>
In the capital of Islamabad, a Flood Relief Center has been
established to collect information on rivers' water position and
people affected by rains across the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
