<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Mining Industry Threatened by Sinking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Mines, Environment
and Tourism Secretary Charles Chipato said today the viability of
the mining industry is being threatened by fluctuating mineral
prices.
</P>
<P>
Gold mines in Zimbabwe were the worst affected as the price of
the mineral sank to the lowest in 12 years, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The fall in gold price has resulted in the closing of a number
of marginal mines, while bigger ones have drastically cut their
production levels.
</P>
<P>
According to Chipato, it is important that the mining industry
remains viable for Zimbabwe to achieve its goal of improving the
living standards of the people.
</P>
<P>
He added rising injuries and fatalities in mines were
seriously affecting the socio-economic fabric of mining
communities in Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
"I believe the mining industry needs to re-look at
restructuring their organization and management style in order to
come up with cost effective programs to ameliorate these issues,"
he said. 
</P>
