<HEADLINE> Algeria Alerts People Against Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, August 29 (Xinhua) -- The Algerian government today
alerted its people against terrorist attacks following the
bloodiest massacre overnight committed by Islamic extremists in
the five years of violence in the country.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 villagers in the town of Sidi Moussa, some 20
kilometers south of the capital Algiers, were cut throats,
decapitated or burned by hooded and armed attackers Thursday
night, according to the security service.
</P>
<P>
Most of the victims were women and children, the security
service quoted eyewitnesses as saying. Local residents put the
death toll as high as more than 300, citing that many bodies were
burned during the five-hour-long massacre.
</P>
<P>
However, the government gave an official count this afternoon
of 98 killed and 120 wounded in the terrorist attack near the
capital.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued this afternoon, the government vowed to
take strict measures to protect the rural areas nationwide. It
also vowed to continue its fight against terrorists unswervingly
till they are wiped out.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 people were killed over the last week in a new
escalation of the terrorist acts all over Algeria. About 60,000
people have so far reportedly been slaughtered since violence
erupted in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Rebellions began five years ago after the military-backed
government canceled a parliamentary election in which the Islamic
Salvation Front was poised to win. 
</P>
</TEXT>
