<HEADLINE> China Wins Women's Platform Diving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MESSINA, Sicily, August 29 (Xinhua) -- China won the gold and
bronze medals in the women's platform diving through Chi Meilan and
Wang Xuan respectively.
</P>
<P>
Chi Meilan, who finished only 14th in China's national champions
cup this year, beat all her opponents and the windy weather to total
494.37 points for the gold medal.
</P>
<P>
Chi was the winner of the preliminaries and semi-finals earlier on
Friday and she hit the highest score of 71.34 points in her second
dive in the final, a backward two and a half somersaults at tuck
position with a 2.9 digree of difficulty.
</P>
<P>
The second dive gave Chi a lead of more than 20 points than her
closest rival. After the that the competitions were mainly between
another Chinese Wang Xuan and Julie Danaux of France.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Wang, ranked 17th in the national champions cup,
was runner-up in the morning's preliminaries and afternoon's
semi-finals. But in the finals, she was a bit nervous and faulted
with two of his five dives.
</P>
<P>
Julie Danaux took the chance to overtake Wang with a backward two
and a half somersaults at tuck position which gave her 64.80 points.
</P>
<P>
She went on to take 59.64 points from her last dive to win the
silver medal with a total of 461.40 points. Wang Xuan finished third
at 449.13 points.
</P>
<P>
It was the third gold medal for Chinese female divers. Lu Haisong
won the 1-meter springboard while Zhu Jinhong took the title of the
3-meter springboard on Monday and Wednesday respectively. 
</P>
