</P>
<P>
Vincent Henderson of the United States beat other seven rivals to
wrest the men's 100-meter gold medal with 10.22 seconds. Alexandre
Porkhomovski of Russia took the silver with 10.39 and American
Jonathan Carter was bronze medallist with 10.42.
</P>
<P>
The women's 100m gold went to Greece's Ekaterini Thanou who chalked
up 11.20 seconds, followed by Ukrainean Anjela Kravchenko in 11.34
and Katia Benth of France in 11.35.
</P>
<P>
The World record holder George Emma of Australia captured the women's
pole vault champion with leaping 4.40 meters. She failed to clear
4.57 meters, two centimeters more than her current world record of
4.55 meters.
</P>
<P>
China's Cai Weiyan, bronze medallist of the indoor world
championshis, was the runner-up with 4.30 meters and Austrian Doris
Auer came third with 4.10 meters.
</P>
<P>
Belarus' Vladimir Doubrovchtchik took The men's discus throw gold
with 66.40 meters and American Andrew Bloom got the silver with 63.12
meters.
</P>
<P>
