Sosimenko was third with 65.02m.
</P>
<P>
The world championship silver winner South African Llewelyn Herbert
wrested the men's 400m hurdels gold medal with a time of 48.99
seconds. Russian Rousian Machtchenko finished second in 49.36 and
world junior championships gold medallist Qatar's Mubarak Faraj was
third in 49.48.
</P>
<P>
The women's 400m hurdles champion went to Ukrainean Tatiana
Terechtchouk who ranked 4th in the world, was timed in 54.91 seconds,
ahead of Russian Ekaterina Bakhvalova in 55.91, and Cuban Daii
Pernia in 56.13.
</P>
<P>
In the last event of women's 10,000m final, Deena Drossin of the
United States was timed with 33 minutes 45.31 seconds for the title.
Italian Luilla Andreucci finished second with 33:54.22 and Japan's
Miwako Yamanaka took third place with 34:10.28.
</P>
<P>
After four days of competition, Russia has kept the top place with
five gold medals. The United States and Ukraine ranked second with
same three golds, and Cuba, South Africa and Belarus took two golds
each.
</P>
<P>
The world sprint festival will be held on August 30 and 31, with
Saturday holding men's ad women's 200 meters races and Sunday
competing in men's and women's 100m events. 
</P>
