<HEADLINE> International Broadcasting Show to Open in Berlin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, August 29 (Xinhua) -- The world's largest consumer
electronics and broadcasting technology exhibition -- the
International Broadcasting Fair (IFA), will open to the public
from Saturday to September 7 in Berlin, organizers said today.
</P>
<P>
The IFA, which is a biennial event, features 812 exhibitors
from 33 countries this year, with Russia, Egypt and India present
for the first time.
</P>
<P>
The catchword of this year's show is digitalization of
broadcasting technologies. 
</P>
