<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Olympic Champion Beaten Again in Universiade Swimming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champion and world
record holder Penelope Heyns of South Africa suffered her second
defeat at the Universiade swimming tournament on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Heyns, who holds the world record of 1:07.02 in the women's 100
meters breaststroke, finished only second in her specialty with
1:10.15.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Heyns was only fourth in the 200 meters breaststroke
final.
</P>
<P>
The event was won by Ukrainian Svitlana Bondarenko who clocked
1:10.02.
</P>
<P>
For the first time since the beginning of the swimming tournament,
Japan failed to win a gold on Friday. The only medals they got were a
silver and a bronze.
</P>
<P>
Swimmers from East European countries dominated the swimming
competitions on Friday as Ukraine got two golds, Slovakia and Poland
got one each.
</P>
<P>
Denis Silantev of Ukraine won the gold in the men's 100 meters
butterfly. Martina Moravcova of Slovakia won the women's 100 meters
freestyle at 55.47. The women's 200 meters butterfly title went to
Anna Uryniuk of Poland.
</P>
<P>
The American team kept their winning form on Friday as they took
the men's 4X100 meters freestyle relay with a modest time of 3:21.17,
some 6 seconds off the world record set by the Americans in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Brazil also got a share of swimming gold when Luiz Eduardo Lima won
the men's 400 meters freestyle title with a time of 3:53.91.
</P>
<P>
The track and field competitions suffered from a windy weather. But
world record holder Emma George of Australia still managed to clear
the 4.40 meters for the gold of women's pole vault.
</P>
<P>
Cai Weiyan, former world record holder from China, finished second
at 4.30 meters.  Doris Auer of Austria vaulted to her personal best
of 4.10 meters to snatch the bronze medal.
</P>
<P>
The men's 100 meters was won by American Vincent Henderson who
clocked 10.22 seconds in the final. The women's 100 meters title went
to Ekaterini Thanou of Germany who was timed at 11.20.
</P>
<P>
The men's discus throw final was dominated by Vladimir
Doubrovchtchik of Belarus who took the title with his best throw of
66.40 meters.
</P>
<P>
Deena Drossin of the United States enjoyed a great advantage as she
finished the women's 10,000 meters race at 33:45.31, some 9 seconds
ahead second-placed Lucilla Andreucci of Italy.
</P>
<P>
Michaela Melinte of Romania met little challenge in the women's
hammer. She won the title with a result of 69.84 meters.
</P>
<P>
The men's and women's 400 meters hurdles were won by South African
Llewellyn Herbert and Ukrainian Tatiana Terechtchouk respectively.
</P>
<P>
The soccer tournament ended on Friday with hosts Italy beat South
Korea 1-0 for the title. The winner came in the second half of extra
time.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Friday, the American eleven edged Ukraine 2-1 for the
bronze medal of the soccer tournament.
</P>
<P>
The strong wind in Messina posed a great threat to women's platform
divers. But Chinese diver Chi Meilan still managed to stage a superb
performance including a perfect dive which gave her 71.34 points.
</P>
<P>
Chi Meilan won the title with a total of 494.37 points. It was the
third diving gold for the Chinese female divers.
</P>
<P>
Julie Danaux of France won the silver medal at 461.40, followed by
Wang Xuan of China in the third place at 449.13.
</P>
<P>
The women's volleyball and basketball tournaments came to an end on
Friday with the Russian team won the volleyball title after beating
their American opponents 3-0 in the final.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal of the women's volleyball went to Japan, which
downed Canada 3-0 in the third-place playoff.
</P>
<P>
The women's basketball tournament ended with the Americans taking
the gold. They beat Cuba 100-82 for the title. Czech Republic
finished third with a 69-37 victory Italy.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine won its fourth fencing title after beating Hungary 45-39 in
the men's epee team final. Poland won the bronze medal after
trouncing Russia 45-31 in the playoff.
</P>
<P>
The fencing tournament will end on Saturday after the women's foil
team finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
