<HEADLINE> Nebiolo Hurt in Car Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 29 (Xinhua) -- The International
Amateur Athletics Federation President Primo Nebiolo was slightly
injured on Friday when his car was hit by a police car answering
an emergency call, Italian police said.
</P>
<P>
Nebiolo, also the head of International University Sports
Association, was taken to hospital suffering from a bruised arm
after the accident in the east coast town of Catania.
</P>
<P>
His wife Giovanna, who was travelling with her husband in the
back seat, was also taken to hospital with a broken shoulder, a
police officer said.
</P>
<P>
An IAAF spokesman, in Sicily for the World Student Games, said
Nebiolo was only slightly injured but would be kept in hospital
for routine x-rays.
</P>
<P>
"Mr Nebiolo's fine. He wasn't seriously hurt," he said.
</P>
<P>
Nebiolo, 74, was travelling to Palermo, on the other side of
this Mediterranean island, when the crash happened.
</P>
<P>
The Turin lawyer was going to watch Italy play South Korea in
the final of the Games soccer tournament.
</P>
<P>
Nebiolo had been due to give a news conference on Saturday
ahead of this weekend's finale to the Games.
</P>
<P>
He was then due to travel to Switzerland for next week's vital
International Olympic Committee (IOC) meeting at which the winning
candidate for the 2004 Games will be named. 
</P>
