<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NationsBank to Buy Barnett Banks for 15.5 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. fourth largest bank,
NationsBank, said on Friday it would acquire Florida's Barnett
Banks for 15.5 billion U.S. dollars in stock, creating the
country's third biggest bank.
</P>
<P>
The acquisition of Florida's largest bank helps NationsBank
become an even stronger powerhouse in the Southeast. Combined with
Barnett, its Florida operations alone would rank as the country's
10th-biggest.
</P>
<P>
After the deal which is the biggest ever in the U.S. banking
industry, NationsBank would rank only behind Chase Manhattan and
Citicorp, replacing BankAmerica as the No. 3 banking company in
the country. The previous biggest banking deal was Wells Fargo &AMP;
Co.'s 14.2 billion dollars buy of First Interstate Bancorp.
</P>
<P>
The new merger, which needs federal government review, is
expected to be completed early next year, the companies said.
</P>
<P>
Barnett Banks, with 44 billion dollars in assets, has more than
600 branches in Florida and south Georgia and about 22,000
employees. The company offers consumer lending in 41 states,
concentrating its business in Florida.
</P>
<P>
It controls about 20 percent of deposits in Florida followed by
First Union Corporation of Charlotte, North Carolina, with 17
percent, NationsBank with 12 percent and SunTrust Banks of Atlanta
with 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
NationsBank operates 2,600 branches in 16 states -- mostly in
the Southeast and Midwest -- and the District of Columbia and has
assets of 240 billion dollars. It has 80,000 employees, including
8,000 in Florida.
</P>
<P>
NationsBank announced its acquisition of Montgomery Securities
in June. The purchase of Montgomery, which is based in San
Francisco, would help the bank to join with other lenders and
enter the securities business, which is benefiting from the bull
market on the Wall Street. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
