<HEADLINE> Thorpe Beats Perkins in Novelty Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The 14-year-old Australian Ian
Thorpe beat Olympic champion Kieren Perkins in a novelty swimming
event in Sydney on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Thorpe beat Perkins, world record holder at 400 and 1,500
meters freestyle to win a newly-designed 400 meters freestyle
event which was divided into two 200 races held a minute apart.
</P>
<P>
Perkins won the second heat but Thorpe, who finished second in
both heats, had the best overall time of three minutes 47.07
seconds, 5.50 seconds faster than fellow Australian Perkins.
</P>
<P>
Other winners included Olympic champions Alexander Popov of
Russia, Michelle de Bruin of Ireland and Claudia Poll of Costa
Rica.
</P>
<P>
Double Olympic champion Popov won a 50 meters freestyle contest
staged in a series of elimination races, with the last-placed
swimmer in each heat dropping out until the winner was decided.
</P>
<P>
Atlanta Olympic three golds holder De Bruin won the women's 200
individual medley and Poll won the women's 400 freestyle ahead of
Australia's Susie O'Neill. 
</P>
</TEXT>
