<HEADLINE> France Evacuates Personnel from Embassy in Brazzaville </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 30 (Xinhua) -- France today evacuated its
personnel from the French embassy in Brazzaville to another
district of the capital of Congo Republic, announced the French
Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
"The confrontations in Brazzaville and the risks which result
from it, the deterioration of the working conditions of our
personnel, have brought France to decide to withdraw provisionally
the activities of the diplomatic chancellery to the residence of
the ambassador situated in the district of Bocongo," said a
French Foreign Ministry communique.
</P>
<P>
It said that the French ambassador to the Congo Republic
Raymond Cesaire, who is one of the few foreign envoys who have not
withdrawn from there, and his colleagues are continuing their
task.
</P>
<P>
The French embassy is located at the division line between the
warring factions, along which troops loyal to President Pascal
Lissouba and militiamen supporting General Denis Sassou N'guesso
have been shooting at each other with heavy weapons.
</P>
<P>
The residence of the French ambassador, "Case de Gaulle," is
so far saved from the shooting range. 
</P>
