<HEADLINE> Liao Hui, Tung Chee Hwa Meet in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Director of the Hong Kong and
Macao Affairs Office under the State Council Liao Hui and
Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) Tung Chee Hwa met here today in Shenzhen to discuss related
issues concerning the relationship between the HKSAR and the
Central People's Government.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press briefing prior to the meeting, Liao said that
since the handover of Hong Kong two months ago, everything has
been going on very well in the HKSAR, with social stability and
economic prosperity well maintained.
</P>
<P>
"The HKSAR government led by Mr. Tung has been operating very
successfully and efficiently. Today's Hong Kong is better than
yesterday, and it will surely have an even better tomorrow," Liao
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that his office will help communicate relations between
the HKSAR government and the Central People's Government, as well as
all the departments in the central government and various
localities. The office will serve the HKSAR government and the Hong
Kong public, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa said that for years the Hong Kong and Macao
Affairs Office devoted to the establishment of the HKSAR, laying a
 solid foundation for today's good operation of the HKSAR
government.
</P>
<P>
He said that both the HKSAR government and Hong Kong citizens are
ready to meet various challenges of the new millennium and are
committed to Hong Kong's development in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Both Liao and Tung said that the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs
Office and the HKSAR government should maintain close relations
and good communications.
</P>
<P>
This is their first meeting since Liao Hui assumed the post of
director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office. 
</P>
