<HEADLINE> U.S. Reconnaissance Flights Surge Over DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The United States has
conducted about 160 air reconnaissance missions over the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) this month, the
Korean Central News Agency (KCNA) quoted military sources as
saying today.
</P>
<P>
The official news agency said that on Thursday morning, an E-3
early-warning plane flew over the Korean Peninsula in coordination
with the on-going joint military exercises code-named "Ulji Focus
Lens" between the U.S. and South Korea.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a Japan-based U.S. RC-135 strategic spy plane flew
over the north-south demarcation line on Friday, taking pictures
and eavesdropping strategic facilities in the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
Among all the reconnaissance flights this month, about 20
sorties were carried out by U.S. strategic planes and
early-warning planes based in American overseas military bases,
KCNA said.
</P>
<P>
Such reconnaissance activities pose a serious challenge to the
peaceful reunification of the DPRK and South Koreas and should be
stopped unconditionally and immediately, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
