<HEADLINE> Doohan Sets to Win his 11th Title This Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Australian Michael Doohan took
pole position on Saturday at Brno for the 500cc Czech Grand Prix,
which made him on the way to equal Italian Giacomo Agostini's 11
wins in one season.
</P>
<P>
Doohan has won 10 of the 11 races this year, which means that
he has already won his fourth consecutive world champion.
</P>
<P>
He trailed Italy's Luca Cadalora and Spaniard Sete Gibernau
with only 10 minutes remaining of the hour-long qualifying session
on a wet and blustery day. But he emerged from the pits to post
three consecutive fastest laps to earn pole position.
</P>
<P>
Doohan flew around the Masaryk circuit on his Honda in a best
time of two minutes 14.105 seconds, 1.090 seconds ahead of
Cadalora on a Yamaha.
</P>
<P>
France's Jean Michel Bayle finished third 1.233 seconds off
the pace on a Modenas KR3. And Gibernau dropped to fifth on his
Yamaha behind the Suzuke of Australian Daryl Beattie. 
</P>
</TEXT>
