<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ballanger Takes Another Gold in World Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- French Felicia Ballanger won
the women's 500m time trial gold medal with a time of 34.684
seconds at the World Track Cycling Championships in Perth,
Australia.
</P>
<P>
It is Ballanger's third-straight title in this event and her sixth
world championship triumph overall.
</P>
<P>
Australian Michelle Ferris, second-last starter in the 17-rider
field, won the silver medal. Ferris rode a brilliant time of
35.719 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Magali Faure of France took the bronze with a time of 35.898,
followed by Cuihua Jiang of China 35.930.
</P>
<P>
Ballanger had won the previous two world titles in the sprint
as well and her double victory here proved that she is unbeatable
in the world right now.
</P>
<P>
France has raked up five golds, followed by Australia with one
gold, two silvers and one bronze.
</P>
<P>
The 4,000m team prusuit saw a dramatic finish in the 4,000m
team pursuit final when the leading Ukrainian team crashed in the
late stage.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine, which badly need to win a world gold medal, led the
Italians by more than a second off the home bend with only three
laps left.
</P>
<P>
But the second rider in the pace line clipped the wheel in
front of him, falling and bringing down his two compatriots behind
him. No one was badly injured, but the accident shattered the
team's winning hope.
</P>
<P>
Italy took the advantage to win the event in 4 minutes 10.225
seconds, with France taking the bronze medal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
