<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-30 14:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan President to Visit Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 30 (Xinhua) -- President of Kazakhstan
Nursultan Nazarbayev will start a two-day official visit to
Kuwait Sunday during which several economic agreements are
expected to be signed, Kuwait News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
This will be Nazarbayev's first visit to the Gulf country
since he assumed power in December 1991. He will also pay visits
to Bahrain and Oman following his visit to Kuwait, the agency
said.
</P>
<P>
The Kazakh president is to hold talks with Kuwaiti Amir Sheikh
Jaber Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah and other Kuwaiti leaders on boosting
bilateral relations in the field of politics, economy, trade and
investment.
</P>
<P>
The agreements to be signed will cover economy, trade,
investment and avoiding double taxation.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev, who will be accompanied by a high-powered
political and economic delegation, is also expected to call on
Kuwaiti businessmen to invest in Kazakhstan by taking the
advantage of preferential policies offered by Kazakhstan to
foreign investors, including a five-year total tax exemption
period and a 10-year profit taxes exemption period.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Kuwait and Kazakhstan have been developing
steadily since the former Soviet Union republic became independent
in 1991.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, Kuwait Minister of Finance Nasser Abdullah Al-Rudhan
visited Kazakhstan and signed a memorandum of understanding under
which Kuwait would support Kazakhstan with expertise in the field
of oil exploration while Kazakhstan would supply Kuwait with mine
sweeping experts.
</P>
<P>
Kazakh Foreign Minister Kasymzhomart Tokayev visited Kuwait in
May 1997 during which he delivered a message from Nazarbayev to
the Kuwaiti Amir on bilateral relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
