<HEADLINE> 11th Panchen Lama Presides Over Buddhist Ceremonies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The 11th Panchen Lama, Panchen
Erdeni Losang Jizum Qamba Lhunzhub Qoigyijiabu, presided over
Tibetan Buddhist rites here today to mark the 10th anniversary of
the founding of the China Advanced Tibetan Buddhism College.
</P>
<P>
The seven-year-old Panchen performed the rites at the Xihuang
Temple which was built for his predecessor, the 5th Panchen Lama,
who journeyed to Beijing in 1652 to pay his respects to the Qing
Dynasty Emperor. The college is located in the temple.
</P>
<P>
The 11th Panchen told the 200-odd Living Buddhas and eminent
monks in attendance that "We should do a better job in running the
college to cultivate more Tibetan buddhists who love the
motherland and the religion".
</P>
<P>
The China Advanced Tibetan Buddhism College was established
according to the wishes of late 10th Panchen Lama, Bainqen Ordini
Qoigyi Gyaincain.  
</P>
