<HEADLINE> Harbin-Jiamusi Highway Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The 324-km Harbin-Jiamusi
section of the first-class new Harbin-Tongjiang highway opened to
traffic today, 13 months ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Development Bank (ADB) provided a loan of 142 million
US dollars for construction of the section. Construction commenced
in May 1995 and was completed today, costing 3.36 billion yuan
(404.81 million US dollars). ADB awarded the project a Triple-A
rating for construction progress and efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The section is part of the 572.2-km Harbin-Tongjiang highway
which will eventually link Harbin, capital of Heilongjiang
Province, and Tongjiang in the province, a key highway
project scheduled for completion in the province during the
Ninth Five-Year-Plan period (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
The Harbin-Jiamusi link is expected to greatly benefit economic
development in eastern and western areas of Heilongjiang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
