<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Calls for Better Performance by Township Coal Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo
today urged the country's township coal mines to carry out
structural readjustments and promote healthy development in
accordance with the Law on Coal.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to the ongoing national coal conference, Wu said
the establishment of key coal-producing counties presents an
effective method for transforming township coal enterprises and
introducing mass production.
</P>
<P>
Wu called for various localities to fully implement State
Council policies on supporting, transforming, reorganizing and
enhancing township coal mines in order to promote their sound
development.
</P>
<P>
In 1987, the government designated 112 key coal-producing
counties out of 1,257 related counties nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The key coal-producing counties, which have recorded notable
achievements over the past 10 years, produced 274 million tons of
coal in 1996, or 20 percent of the nation's total coal production.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, these counties recorded a total output value of 18.42
billion yuan, with taxes and profits of 1.17 billion yuan and 1.4
billion yuan respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
