<HEADLINE> Syrian Defense Minister on Realization of Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Defense Minister
General Mustafa Talas has said his country gave top priority to
the realization of fair and comprehensive peace in the Middle
East.
</P>
<P>
Local press today quoted Talas as saying at the ceremony of
the naval force day Friday in the coastal city of Latakia that
fair and comprehensive peace can never be established unless the
Israeli expansionist policy is ended and the occupied Arab
territories are returned to their owners.
</P>
<P>
He said Syria deems the realization of peace its strategic
option because peace is the only thing that can get the region
out of the violence circle.
</P>
<P>
Since it came to power last year, the Israeli government led
by Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu sought to undermine the
peace process and keep the region in the whirlwind of struggle,
Talas said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the U.S. administration to pressure the Netanyahu
government and force it to comply with the will of the
international community and implement U.N. Security Council
resolutions.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian defense minister reiterated that his country would
never give up a grain of its sand and would never be intimidated
by threats.
</P>
<P>
Syria will keep faithful to its principles in defense of the
dignity of the Arab nation till its all usurped rights are
regained, he concluded. 
</P>
