<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Records Remarkable Achievements (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Extensive efforts to build an
army with Chinese characteristics over the the past five years
have yielded remarkable results in modernizing and standardizing
the People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
9,936 training classes held over the past five years have
benefitted a total of 464,000 officers at or above the regimental
commander level.
</P>
<P>
The seven theoretical study and discussion sessions the PLA has
sponsored to improve the theoretical level of military personnel
have produced 93 theses, which were later selected to be presented
at national seminars, with five winning various types of awards.
</P>
<P>
Study sessions sponsored by the PLA has yielded over 70 types
of theoretical study and audio-visual materials.
</P>
<P>
The PLA has recorded great progress in efforts to improve the
leadership of the Communist Party of China (CPC) in the army.
</P>
<P>
The vast majority of secretaries of the CPC committees at or
above the division commander level and over 54,000 secretaries of
basic units in PLA participated in training classes during the
1992-1996 period.
</P>
<P>
The PLA has acted in accordance with instructions made by
Chairman Jiang Zemin of the Central Military Commission, at the
end of 1994 and has launched an education campaign designed to
enhance the sense of patriotism and devotion, strengthen the
revolutionary outlook, stress the respect for officers and the
love for soldiers, and uphold the spirit of hard work.
</P>
<P>
Over 200 officers at or above the army commander level and over
6,000 lower-ranking officers have undertaken fact-finding missions
to PLA grass-roots units on an annual basis.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970830.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Records Remarkable Achievements (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A number of officers and soldiers have been cited as the models
to emulate and over 10,000 model grass-roots units and individuals
have been named following Jiang Zemin's call for the army to take
the lead in promoting ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
A large number of qualified young officers have been promoted
to higher ranks. The average age of the military commanders has
dropped by two years compared to 1992, registering a 17.8 percent
increase of officers with college or higher educations.
</P>
<P>
The increasingly widely-spread use of high-tech items such as
computer simulation has led to significant improvements in
military training. In addition, constant improvements in military
equipment, and the overall structure and combat readiness of land,
air and naval forces have been made.
</P>
<P>
Improvements in military legislation has led to the
promulgation of a group of military laws, rules and regulations.
</P>
<P>
Improved logistics and relevant technology resulted in the
formation of a strong logistical support system for supplies,
salvage, transportation and maintenance, and has greatly improved
the life of soldiers stationed in remote areas.
</P>
<P>
In addition, new highways, railways and airports have produced
a three-dimensional transportation network for national defense.
</P>
<P>
Major breakthroughs have recorded in scientific research
related to national defense, with the most representative
achievements including successful launches of the Dongfanghong-3
and the Fengyun-2 satellites and the introduction of advanced
mainframe computers.
</P>
<P>
Remarkable results have also been made in the realm of military
diplomacy, with PLA sending delegations to over 80 countries since
1992. The PLA has also hosted visits by several hundred foreign
military delegations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
