<HEADLINE> Thai Champion Defends IBF Mini-flyweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANKOK, Agust 30 (Xinhua) -- Reigning Thai champion Ratanaphon
Dutchboygym successfully defended his International Boxing
Federation (IBF) mini-flyweight title with a convincing victory at
Nong Khai, Thailand, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old Thai, defeated No. 7 contender Wellington
Vincente, 21, of Brazil with a technical knockout two minutes 55
seconds into the second round in his seventh title defence in the
northeastern Thai town.
</P>
<P>
American referee Abraham Pachenko intervened to stop the fight
after the stocky Ratanaphon launched a long series of 32 punches
to the head of the ultimately helpless Vincente.
</P>
<P>
By this victory, Ratanaphon improved his record to 34 wins (25
KOs), one draw and two losses, while Vincente suffered his first
loss on 11 wins (five KOs). 
