<HEADLINE> Algerian PM Condemns Largest Massacre </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Algerian Prime Minister Ahmed
Ouyahya has condemned the massacre by terrorists in Sedi Moussa
town, south of the capital Algiers, Thursday night as "barbaric
and coward act of reprisal," the Algerian radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
An unidentified armed group perpetrated a horrible massacre
Thursday night in the small town that lies at about 20 kilometers
south of Algiers, killing 98 local people and wounding 120
others, according to the government figures.
</P>
<P>
However, eyewitnesses put the number of deaths in this
mass-murder incident at more than 200. The massacre is the
largest terrorist act witnessed by Algeria at the hands of armed
groups over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian radio quoted Ouyahya as saying that the
government would carry on its fight against the criminal
terrorists till they are eradicated completely.
</P>
<P>
This massacre is, like the previous terrorist acts, a mere
barbaric and coward reprisal targeting the sons of Algeria that
stood firm against the ugly face of terrorism, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian prime minister noted that his government
was taking strict measures to boost security around the remote
rural areas nationwide.
</P>
<P>
Islamic militants have been waging a war against the
government since 1992 when the government canceled elections that
the Islamic Salvation Front was believed to win. More than 60,000
people have been killed in the five years of insurgency.
</P>
</TEXT>
