<HEADLINE> China-St. Lucia Diplomatic Ties Appreciated: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Shen Guofang said here today that the Chinese government
highly appreciates St. Lucia's decision on "severing diplomatic
ties" with Taiwan and establishing diplomatic relations with the
People's Republic of China (PRC).
</P>
<P>
Shen said that the establishment of diplomatic ties between
China and St. Lucia is in the fundamental interests and desire of
the two peoples, and China has decided to establish diplomatic
relations with St. Lucia on September 1 on the basis of the Five
Principles of Peaceful Co-Existence.
</P>
<P>
Shen said he believes that there are broad prospects for the
development of Sino-St. Lucia friendship and cooperation in
various fields.
</P>
<P>
St. Lucia Prime Minister Kenny Anthony made an announcement on
August 29 that his country decided to sever the so-called
"diplomatic ties" with Taiwan and forge diplomatic ties with the
PRC.
</P>
<P>
Anthony said that most countries in the world have diplomatic
links with the PRC, and in the view of the international law,
there cannot be two governments in one country.
</P>
<P>
St. Lucia decided to follow the current world trend to
establish diplomatic ties with the PRC, hoping to develop
bilateral friendship and cooperation in various fields, Anthony
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
