<HEADLINE> Rebels Kill 10, Abduct 70 in West Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of the Allied Democratic
Forces (ADF) raided a trading center in west Uganda, killing 10
and abducting other 70, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The attack in early morning Friday on Kihondo trading center
in Kabarole district was confirmed by Charles Agina,
the operation commander in the district, and Davis Mudaali, the
regional police commander.
</P>
<P>
"My officers and men have joined the army to pursue the
rebels," Mudaali said.
</P>
<P>
The rebels ransacked the trading center at least one and a half
hours, witnesses said.
</P>
<P>
"Various shops were broken into and looted," said Bagwa
whose shop was among the robbed.
</P>
<P>
One rebel was killed in the exchange of fire, and one soldier was
killed by a landmine when the army pursued the rebels.
</P>
<P>
This was the first serious harassment of the ADF rebels to
Kabarole district.
</P>
<P>
ADF is a rebel group haunting in Kasese district in the west. In
mid-June, ADF sent a detachment to West Bundibugyo district to
develop a food source but the attempt was foiled by Uganda
authorities. ADF has some 300 members, an earlier official report
said.
</P>
<P>
ADF had some 1,500 soldiers last November. 
</P>
</TEXT>
