<HEADLINE> Cook Visit Strengthens Ties Between Philippines, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today said the three-day visit here of British Foreign Secretary
Robin Cook would further strengthen the relations between the
Philippines and the United Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
"I think this visit of Minister Robin Cook representing the new
Labor government in the UK augurs well for our enhanced relations
between the UK and the Philippines," Ramos told newsmen after his
luncheon meeting with Cook.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Foreign Affairs Undersecretary Rodolfo Severino said
the topics discussed during the luncheon included politics and
developments in the region.
</P>
<P>
Severino said Cook expressed confidence in the Philippine
economy and briefed Ramos about the Asia-Europe meeting scheduled
in London in April of next year.
</P>
<P>
Ramos also wished that British Prime Minister Tony Blair can
visit the Philippines, Severino said.
</P>
<P>
Cook, who arrived Friday on the first ever visit to the
Philippines, will be in Manila until Sunday. He will hold talks
with his counterpart Domingo Siazon.
</P>
<P>
The British Foreign Secretary is visiting Manila as part of a
tour of four Asian countries. It is also his first official trip
outside Europe and North America.  
</P>
