</P>
<P>
-- The civil war in Algeria, or rather the martyrdom which has
lived the population of the country over the past five years, has
reached its limit of horror and taken a new turning point. From 100
to 300 civilians -- according to different accounts -- were burned
alive, had their throats cut or mutilated by axes in Reis, 20
kilometers from the center of Algiers, in an unprecedented barbarity
which lasted for four hours at dawn on Friday.
