<HEADLINE> Cambodian King Has Role to Restore Peace: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Foreign Minister
Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said today that ASEAN is confident that
Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk can play a role in restoring peace
and stability in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
King Sihanouk still has influence and is respected in that
country, he said, hoping that the situation in Cambodia would
normalize with his (King's) return to Phnom Penh.
</P>
<P>
"ASEAN feels that King Sihanouk still has that role to play to
enable the country to reach national reconciliation," he was
quoted by the Malaysian national news agency Bernama as saying
today in the northern state of Pulau Pinang.
</P>
<P>
"There are still clashes in the northern part of the country
near the Thai border," Abdullah told reporters there, adding if
clashes and military actions cease to occur, there is a
possibility that peace and stability could be fully restored in
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
