<HEADLINE> Minimum Wage Rises in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's monthly minimum wage
will increase to 760 Zimbabwe Dollars (66 U.S. Dollars), up from
400 Zimbabwe Dollars per month, according to the announcement
made here Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the government Gazette, the new wage comes into
effect from July 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
The minimum wage is earned by the workers whose remuneration
is not fixed by any agreement or regulation under the Labor
Rrelations Act.
</P>
<P>
However, the new minimum wage falls far below the demands of
trade unions who say a salary below 1,000 Zimbabwe Dollars (86
U.S. Dollars) per month can no longer sustain anyone.
</P>
<P>
The government also gazetted new wages for other workers with
a 31.22 percent increase. 
</P>
