<HEADLINE> Uganda's Population Shoots up to 20.4 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's population has
increased by 22 percnet from 16.7 million in 1991 to 20.4 million
this year, a local daily '' The New Vision'' today.
</P>
<P>
Jothan Musinguzi, Director of the Population Secretariat was
quoted as saying that this figure would double by the year 2025.
He stressed the need for proper family planning in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Fiftyseven percent of the Ugandans now live below
the poverty line, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that the fast growth of population has resulted in poor
feeding, low rates of immunisation against killer diseases and
limited practice of family planning.
</P>
<P>
Uganda, with 43 percent teenage pregnances, has the highest
rate of such on the continent of Africa.
</P>
<P>
The fertility rate per woman in Uganda is 6.8 children.
</P>
</TEXT>
