<HEADLINE> Liaoning Eliminates Unreasonable Fees for Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province has effectively improved its environment for overseas
investment by eliminating unreasonable fees.
</P>
<P>
The province has cancelled 118 unreasonable fees targeted at
overseas-funded enterprises since April last year, according to a
provincial official.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that unreasonable fees in the past undermined
Liaoning's investment environment, and added that the province
improved its soft investment environment in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The investment environment has improved remarkably owing to the
concerted efforts of the related departments, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that Liaoning had actually put to use
2.1 billion US dollars in overseas investment last year, up 10
percent on 1995, with direct foreign investments rising by 18.7
percent to 1.7 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, overseas-funded enterprises in
Liaoning reported a sales volume of 26 billion yuan (3.1 billion
US dollars) for the first half of this year, an increase of 21.5
percent over the same period of last year.  
</P>
