<HEADLINE> West African States to Check Rising Cross-border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, August 30 (Xinhua) --Leaders of west African states
have promised to make great efforts to fight rising drug abuses
and cross-border crimes in the sub-region.
</P>
<P>
At the 20th summit of the of the Economic Community of West
African States (ECOWAS) ended here this morning, heads of state
and government expressed their concern over the rapid spread of
drug abuse in the region and the increasing role of West Africa
as a transit center for international drug trafficking.
</P>
