<HEADLINE> UNDP Administrator Due in Pakistan on September 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Administrator of the United
Nations Development Program (UNDP) James Gustave Speth will be in
Pakistan Monday for a four-day visit to the country.
</P>
<P>
Speth, who has been confirmed by the UN General Assembly in May
for a second term as UNDP Administrator, will be visiting Pakistan
for the first time, said a press release issued by UNDP offices
here today.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Speth will meet President Farooq Leghari,
Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, Finance Minister Sartaj Aziz and
other senior officials, the release said.
</P>
<P>
Speth, who was first appointed as UNDP Administrator in 1993,
will sign several new UNDP programs which are aimed to reinforce
national development efforts in Pakistan, it said.
</P>
<P>
With offices in 132 developing countries, UNDP is the world's
largest multilateral source of grant technical assistance. It
manages about 2 billion US dollars annually and focuses its work
primarily on poverty elimination, good governance and
environmental regulation.  
</P>
