<HEADLINE> 14 Die as Bus Plunges into River in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- At least 14 Bangladeshi people,
including two women and five children, were killed Friday when a
mini-bus fell into river in Manikganj, about 50 kilometers
northwest of the capital Dhaka, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Some thirty injured passengers were admitted to local hospital
while many more passengers were still missing as they were feared
washed away by strong current of the swollen river Isamati.
</P>
<P>
The mini-bus met the accident when the driver lost control over
the crowded Dhaka-Aricha passenger bus ignoring the speed-breaker
at top speed, said local police sources.
</P>
<P>
In another road accident also on Friday, three persons,
including a rising film actress Shyama, were killed and four
injured in Dhaka, according to the police sources. 
</P>
