<HEADLINE> ECOWAS Promises Continued Support for Liberia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The heads of state and government
of the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) have
promised to support Liberia in its post-war rebuilding.
</P>
<P>
The leaders made the promise at the closing session of the
ECOWAS summit ended early this morning at the Nigerian capital
Abuja.
</P>
<P>
The heads of state and government of ECOWAS congratulated
Liberia on its ending of seven years civil war and successfully
conducting the election on multi-party basis.
</P>
<P>
They called on Liberian leader Charles Taylor to continue his
policy of national reconciliation and unity.
</P>
<P>
The summit urged the Liberian people, the ECOWAS member
countries as well as the whole international society to support
Liberia in its resettlement of refugees, national reconciliation
and reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
The ECOWAS announced that it has lifted all sanctions on
Liberia and requested the international society to do the same.
</P>
<P>
It agreed to extend the tenure of the ECOWAS peace-keeping
force in Liberia, upon receiving request from the Liberian
government.
</P>
<P>
It directed the ECOWAS Executive Secretariat to participate in
the formulation and monitoring of the implementation of the
reconstruction program in Liberia. 
</P>
