<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Huge Loan Provided for Expressway Construction in Hainan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Loans worth 900 million yuan (108
million US dollars) have been provided for building part of an
expressway network that encircles south China's Hainan province.
</P>
<P>
The loans offered by the Hainan Branch of the Agricultural Bank
of China (ABC) are expected to be used for construction of the
section linking Yangpu Development Area with Basuo in the western
part of the island province.
</P>
<P>
Hainan has accelerated highway building over recent
years. Besides the completion of the eastern part of a
round-the-island expressway, the section linking Haikou city, the
provincial capital, and Yangpu Development Area of the western
part of the network has open to traffic.
</P>
<P>
The Yangpu-Basuo section, whose construction now under way, is
regarded as a key part of the western link and, upon completion,
it will become a trunk line in the less-developed central and
western Hainan, connecting the four economic areas of Haikou,
Yangpu, Basuo, and Sanya and the coastal regions.
</P>
<P>
The western link is vital to the development of this tropical
island province since the surrounding areas, abundant in mineral
and aquatic resources, is an important base for producing iron and
steel, building materials, cement and plate glass, refined oil and
related petroleum products and other heavy industrial goods.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
