<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOWAS Approves Sanctions Against S.Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The 20th summit of the heads of
states of the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS)
has approved a packages of sanctions and blockade on Sierra Leone
to force its military government to step down.
</P>
<P>
This decision was taken at the closing session of the summit
which ended here this morning.
</P>
<P>
The final communique issued by the summit said the ECOWAS
leaders endorsed the objectives of early reinstatement of the
legitimate government of President Tejan Kabbah, the return of
peace and security and the resolution of the refugee problem.
</P>
<P>
The leaders expressed their determination to deploy all
efforts towards the peaceful resolution of the Sierra Leone
crisis and called for the co-operation and understanding of all
parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
The communique said the leaders are deeply concerned about
the breakdown of negotiations in Abidjan on July 30th between the
ECOWAS Committee of Four on Sierra Leone and the military junta
in that country and decided to approve the sanctions and blockade
in view of the intransigence of the illegal government.
</P>
<P>
The summit mandated the ECOWAS peace-keeping force known as
ECOMOG to monitor the ceasefire, enforce sanctions and embargo
and secure the peace in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
It decided to enlarge the Committee of Four into the committee
of five by including Liberia, and raise the status of the
committee to the level of heads of state and government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
