<HEADLINE> Abacha Elected ECOWAS Chairman for Second Term </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The 20th summit of the heads of
states of the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS)
has elected Nigerian Head of State Sani Abacha as its chairman
for the second term for the 1997/1998 year.
</P>
<P>
This was announced at the closing session of the summit which
ened early this morning in the Nigerian capital Abuja.
</P>
<P>
Abacha was unanimously elected as the head of the regional
organization for the second term for his great performance in his
first term, especially in bringing an end to seven-year-old
Liberian civil war.
</P>
<P>
The summit appointed Lansana Kouyate as the new ECOWAS
Executive Secretary to replace Eduard Benjamin, who is said to
have a health problem.
</P>
<P>
Kouyate's term will start from September 1, 1997 and last for
four years.
</P>
<P>
The summit decided that henceforth ECOWAS will hold its annual
summit twice a year, one at the ECOWAS headquarters in Abuja, and
the other by turns in other member states.
</P>
<P>
It decided that the next summit will be held in July 1998 in
Abuja. 
</P>
</TEXT>
