<DOCNO> XIE19970830.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India to Impose New Excise on Soft Drinks Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 30 (Xinhua) -- India will levy new excise
duty on the country's soft drinks from September 1 this year, a
government official said today.
</P>
<P>
The new excise duty on soft drinks and soda water will be
levied on the basis of the maximum retail price (MRP) declared on
aerated water bottles and containers.
</P>
<P>
The new excise duty comes on the heels of the government's move
to extend the MRP provisions to cosmetics, toilet preparations,
paints and varnishes and footwear. The government has now covered
almost all the consumer goods on which it has reportedly been
losing revenue because of high mark-ups by manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
A series of raids on soft drink manufacturers revealed that
many companies were resorting to under-valuation. Accordingly, the
government has introduced tariff values, an estimate the
government makes for commodities which are difficult to assess.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
