<HEADLINE> 7 Tamil Rebels killed In North Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 30 (Xinhua) -- At least seven Tamil rebels were
 killed on Friday in fighting with government troops in Northern
Province of Sri Lanka, according to a military spokesman today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) fired mortars at the troops manning defenses around
Puliyankulam.
</P>
<P>
The troops retaliated with mortars and artillery fire, killing
at least four rebels northeast of the town.
</P>
<P>
The troops later killed three more rebels in the same area,
while one soldier was wounded.
</P>
<P>
The troops launched an offensive on Puliyankulam on August 19
in an effort to recapture the highway that links the
government-held Vavuniya to Killinochchi further north, a vital
supply route to the North Jaffna Peninsula.  
</P>
