<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Urbanites Going to Countryside to Beat Summer Heat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Residents of Chengdu, capital of
southwest China's Sichuan province tired of this summer's extended
period of stifling heat in the Sichuan Basin have been fleeing to
the countryside on weekends to beat the heat.
</P>
<P>
This new approach to spending weekends has gained instant
popularity amongst local residents who are able to breath some
cool fresh air and have fun hiking, playing chess and fishing in
the nearby suburban haven far from urban noise and congestion.
</P>
<P>
Farmers on the outskirts of Chengdu have introduced a variety
of tourist programs catering to urbanites, including allowing
their guests to pick vegetables in the fields, and serving
daily dishes typically consumed by a rural family.
</P>
<P>
Chengdu tourism officials note that the 75 rural tourist sites
in Pixian County alone host an average of 2,500 visitors daily,
with earnings of well over 70,000 yuan (8,430 US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
