<DOCNO> XIE19970830.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Qualifies for Basketball World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Brazil obtained a berth for
the 1998 basketball World Cup finals here on Friday by beating
Canada 94-82 at the Tournament of the Americas in Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
In other actions, Puerto Rico defeated Cuba 116-81, the United
States outscored Argentina 91-78, and host Uruguay kept its hopes
alive by beating Venezuela 84-77.
</P>
<P>
Brazil took a 10-point lead at half-time and booked its place
in the finals thanks to a 22-point haul form Vanderley.
</P>
<P>
Two more berths will be assured Saturday, with the last one on
Sunday, while the United States has an automatic berth as world
champion.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the U.S. team topped the group with 11 points,
beating Brazil to second with 10 points, while Canada, Puerto Rico
and Venezuela all have nine points.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay, Argentina and Cuba are levelled on eight points each.
</P>
<P>
Jerome Mincy scored 29 points to lead Puerto Rico to a 116-81
victory over Cuba, the third straight victory for the Puerto
Ricans, who previously had lost three in a row and was once in
danger of not making the second round.
</P>
<P>
Luis Pierri scored a game-high 25 points to help Uruguay claw
back from a four-point half-time deficit, keeping alive of its
slim chance of entering the World Cup finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
