<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangzhou to Ban Styrofoam Food Containers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The local government in
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province, has issued
an order banning the use of styrofoam food containers by
restaurants and snack bars.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou will institute the container ban on September 1 in a
move to rid the city of so-called "white pollution".
</P>
<P>
The production, sale, or use of food containers made from
polyethylene or polypropylene will be prohibited because of the
fact that the items cannot be recycled and as a result of
potential sources of pollution.
</P>
<P>
Substitute materials will include environmentally-friendly
materials made of paper or plant fibers. Recyclable plastic
products are not considered to be a suitable substitute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
