<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Tea Exports Earnings Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Earnings from Sri Lanka's tea
exports in the first half of this year exceed 300 million U.S.
dollars, an increase of 18 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
According Sri Lanka's Tea Export Broad today, tea exports
during January-June reached 305.17 million dollars as against
258.6 million dollars in the corresponding period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The country exported 119 million kilograms of tea during the
first half, compared with 113.9 million kilograms in the same
period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Tea is one of Sri Lanka's main export items and the source of
25 percent of its export earnings. The total tea exports last
year were 244 million kilograms.  
</P>
