<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuban Scientists Claim Cancer Control with Scorpion Toxin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Cuba's medical scientists have
made initial success in using scorpion toxin to control cancer,
the weekly magazine "Negocios in Cuba" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,000 persons with several forms of cancer were treated
recently with a compound obtained from the toxin of a scorpion
species living in Baracoa, in the easternmost part of the island.
</P>
<P>
The results have been satisfactory, with the malignant cells of
most patients clearly brought under control and in some cases
destroyed, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier tests made on dogs and white mice also showed that the
toxin can eliminate or diminish the size of natural tumors without
noticeable side effects.
</P>
<P>
Researchers stressed that only the toxin from the blue scorpion
living in Baracoa, and not any another species of scorpion, is
found to have the cancer-controlling effect. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
