</P>
<P>
-- Japan's Supreme Court ruled Friday that the Education
Ministry acted unconstitutionally when it ordered historian Saburo
Ienaga to delete a description in his textbook of biochemical
experiments on humans conducted by Unit 731 of the Imperial
Japanese Army and ordered the government to pay 400,000 yen in
compensation to Ienaga.
</P>
