</P>
<P>
-- Japan's Chief Cabinet Secretary Seiroku Kajiyama will quit
in a cabinet reshuffle expected after Hashimoto's re-election as
president of the Liberal Democratic Party on September 11.
</P>
<P>
Yomiuri:
</P>
<P>
-- Initial budget requests from Japanese ministries and
agencies for fiscal 1998's general account increased 4.1 percent
from fiscal 1997's initial budget to 80.55 trillion yen, the
Finance Ministry said Friday. 
