<HEADLINE> Myanmar Police Urged to Become Powerful Defense Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 30 (Xinhua) -- A senior Myanmar leader has urged
the country's police force to become the most disciplined and
powerful national defense force, the official New Light of Myanmar
newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting of the Committee for Reformation of
Myanmar Police Force Management System, Lt. Gen. Khin Nyunt, first
secretary of the State Law and Order Restoration Council (SLORC),
stressed the need to enhance morale, discipline, moral conducts
and police and military skills of Myanmar Police Force (MPF).
</P>
<P>
He said the MPF should become the second largest, most
disciplined and the reserve force for national defense after the
Tatmadaw (Myanma Defense Services Force).
</P>
<P>
The committee, chaired by Khin Nyunt, was formed in 1994 to
assess and reform existing rules and regulations of the MPF.
</P>
</TEXT>
