<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria to Close Four Air Bases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria has decided to shut down
four air bases because of insufficient funds, Commander of the Air
Force Stefan Popov announced at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
The Bulgarian Air Force cannot keep all its 14 bases running
and has to close the bases in Shtpaklevo, Gabrovnitsa, Uzundzovo
and Balchik. They may close others in the near future, the
Bulgarian Telegraph Agency quoted Popov as saying.
</P>
<P>
At present, fewer than half the planes of the Bulgarian Air
Force are operating normally, while 30 percent of them are
completely out of operation, said Popov.
</P>
<P>
It is impossible to rebuild the air force without a larger
budget, said the commander. 
</P>
</TEXT>
