<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Evander Holyfield will return
to the ring on November 8 when he will face fellow American
heavyweight champion Michael Moorer in Las Vegas.
</P>
<P>
This was the first fight for Holyfield after he was bitten by
Mike Tyson on June 28, and the return match also serves a chance
of revenge for Holyfield who lost his WBA and IBF crowns to Moorer
on April 22, 1994.
</P>
<P>
Promoter Don King said on Friday that details of the fight will
be revealed later in New York.
</P>
<P>
Holyfield, WBA heavyweight champion, is reportedly to win 20
million U.S. dollars to fight Moorer, who holds the IBF version of
the title and will be paid about 8 million dollars. 
