<HEADLINE> Grassroots Effort Urged to Help the Impoverished Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese entrepreneurs are
calling for more effective grassroots programs to help the poor of
the country, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
To reach this end, the entrepreneurs attending a seminar which
concluded yesterday in Beijing published a written proposal.
</P>
<P>
"To help the country's 58 million poverty-stricken population
is an obligation of the whole society, including the private
entrepreneurs," said vice-chairman of Chinese People\s Political
Consultative Conference, at the seminar. Yang is also chairman of
the Foundation for Undeveloped Regions in China.
</P>
<P>
Initiated by nine business people, an organization with the aim
of drawing investment to China's underdeveloped regions was set up
in 1994. It has established branches in all provinces and
implemented a capital investment of three billion yuan (361
million US dollars) to the country's poor areas.
</P>
<P>
Xiangjiang Group is one of the companies Putian County in east
China's Fujian Province to sign contracts with Xiji County in
northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region to set up five
potato-processing plants by the end of 1998, according to the
Daily.
</P>
<P>
The plan expects to increase the county's annual per-capita
income by 300 yuan. By the end of the year 2000, Xiji is expected
to become China's biggest potato producing and processing base.
</P>
</TEXT>
