<DOCNO> XIE19970830.0204 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Honduras to Create Strategic Coffee Reserve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, August 29 (Xinhua) -- The Honduran government will
create a 40,000-quintal coffee reserve, which may require a 4.5
million U.S. dollar investment, to prevent an announced shortage
of the beans, said the Economy and Commerce Ministry sources today.
</P>
<P>
According to sources, the money for the reserve will come from
the National Coffee Funds and the Honduran Coffee Institute.
</P>
<P>
The measure is being taken because most of the coffee harvest
is exported, which has caused a domestic supply deficit.
</P>
<P>
The reserve will also help control coffee smuggling to
neighboring Central American countries, especially El Salvador.
</P>
<P>
Last year, only 7 percent of total production remained at home,
which caused an increase in local prices.
</P>
<P>
Coffee exports for this year have been estimated at 450 million
dollars, which is higher than that of 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
