<HEADLINE> Woodforde Topples Kafelnikov out of U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Australian doubles specialist
Mark Woodforde toppled third seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia in
straight sets at the second round of the U.S. Open tennis
championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Woodforde, who was ranked 43rd in the singles, upended the 1996
French Open champion 6-3, 6-4, 7-6 (7-4).
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov, who won the tournaments in Halle in June and at New
Haven, Connecticut this month, broke first to take the initial
lead but made a stream of errors to ruin his hope of sailing
further in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Woodforde's changeups and angle shots kept the Russian on the
run, with the latter failing to show any evidence of his class as
one of the best players in the world.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov became the fifth men's seed ousted before the third
round. Earlier this week, fourth-seeded Croatian Goran Ivanisevic
and fifth-seeded Thomas Muster of Austria were toppled in the
first and second rounds respectively.
</P>
<P>
Woodforde's third-round rival will be Andre Agassi, former
world number one, who beat Romanian Adrian Voinea 6-0, 6-2, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
The American, who ranked 63rd in the world, lost the last two
clashes between them, including a match this month when the
Australian trounced him out of the quarter-finals in Indianapolis.
</P>
<P>
Women's second seed Monica Seles of the United States edged
Miriam Oremans of the Netherlands 6-1, 6-1 to advance into the
fourth round easily.
</P>
<P>
Ninth seed Mary Pierce of France beat Natasha Zvereva 7-6
(7-2), 6-1 to go for the next round where she will meet Seles.
</P>
<P>
Frenchwoman Sandrine Testud made her straight win over German
Elena Wagner 6-1, 6-1 after she upset fourth-seeded French Open
champion Iva Majoli in the second round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
