<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eight Stranded Miners Rescued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 30 (Xinhua) -- After being stranded underground
in the dark mine for 10 days, eight miners were finally rescued at
Rujigou Mine in northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
According to China Daily today, the eight miners were trapped
in the mine when a great flow of mud and rocks blocked its
entrance on August 13 after a 40-minute heavy rain hit the region.
</P>
<P>
Despite big floods, rescue work continued by a team of more
than 500 people round the clock.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities rushed to the scene to direct the rescue work.
</P>
<P>
The eight men survived on water and fresh air available in the
lane to which they had retreated. And they lay on the ground,
avoiding an excessive drain of their strength.
</P>
<P>
To guide the rescuers, the eight kept one miner's lamp burning
at a time.
</P>
<P>
At last, the rescuers spotted the light in the early morning
hours of August 23. The eight miners were fully conscious when
rescued.
</P>
<P>
And all have made satisfactory recoveries so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970830.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norway Names New National Soccer Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Nils Johan Semb will take the
helm of the Norwegian national soccer squad next summer, the
Norwegian Soccer Federation said in Oslo on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Semb, who has been heading the national under-21 squad for six
years, will replace Egil Olsen who said he had coached the
national squad long enough.
</P>
<P>
In his stint of seven years, Olsen had led the national squad
for 76 international matches, by winning 40 against 15 defeats and
21 draws.
</P>
<P>
Semb, who has signed a four-year contract, has a record of 42
victories, 16 draws and 15 losses.
</P>
<P>
Olsen said he may try to fulfil his dream of coaching a major
foreign soccer team such as Olympique Marseille of France once his
contract runs out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
