<DOCNO> XIE19970830.0220 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, August 30 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The Caribbean nation of Saint Lucia has
decided to establish full diplomatic relations with the People's
Republic of China, according to a press release of the ministry of
Foreign Affairs and International Trade of St. Lucia reaching here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The press release said that the Ministry has informed Taiwan
that the government of Saint Lucia "will be establishing full
diplomatic relations with the People's Republic of China as of
Monday, 1st September 1997."
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Dr. Hon Kenny Anthony will address the nation on
the matter this evening, the press release added.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright will
make her first trip to the Middle East on September 9 to restore
trust between the Palestinians and Israelis so as to pull the
peace process back on track, the State Department announced on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
State Department spokesman James Rubin, in announcing her
maiden official visit to the Middle East, told reporters that the
secretary will "see what she and the United States can do to help
Israel and the Palestinians address the crisis of confidence" and
"explore with the parties how we can again find ways to move
forward towards a comprehensive peace.
</P>
<P>
Albright will also consult with the regional leaders concerned
"about a variety of other important issues, including the security
of the Persian Gulf, the issue of Iran, and the issue of Iraq,
Rubin added.
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- The French navy's aircraft carrier "Foch," which will
replace another carrier "Clemenceau" when the latter retires by
the end of this year, will return to military service by the end
of September.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse (AFP) quoted the Service of Information
and Public Relations of the Army as saying that "Foch," which has
had an overall careenage over the past 18 months in Toulon, is
having its final equipment and material operational verifications.
</P>
<P>
"Foch" will serve until mid-1999, when the new nuclear-powered
aircraft carrier "Charles de Gaulle" enters service.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States Friday reaffirmed that there
will be no role of the Stabilization Forces (SFOR) in Bosnia in
the arrest of the indicted war criminals in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
"That has been official policy from the beginning, that SFOR
troops -- it's not appropriate for SFOR troops to be involved
under the conditions laid out in the Dayton Accords, because
that's not their mission nor their training," said White House
spokesman Joe Lockhart.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Joint Chief of Staff John Shalikashivili said
Thursday that American soldiers would be ill-suited for the role
in the arrest of war suspects in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. fear that its some 8000 soldiers will be in danger if
they go to apprehend the indicted war criminals including former
Bosnian Serb leader Rodavan Karadzic. Two U.S. soldiers were
injured on Thursday in violent clashes with Bosnian Serbs in the
Bosnian town of Brcko. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
