<BODY>
<HEADLINE> St. Lucia Decides to Establish Full Diplomatic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 29 (Xinhua) -- The Caribbean nation of
Saint Lucia has decided to establish full diplomatic relations
with the People's Republic of China, according to a press release
of the ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Trade of St.
Lucia reaching here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The press release said that the Ministry has informed Taiwan
that the government of Saint Lucia "will be establishing full
diplomatic relations with the People's Republic of China as of
Monday, 1st September 1997."
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Dr. Hon Kenny Anthony will address the nation on
the matter this evening, the press release added.
</P>
<P>
The government of the People's Republic of China is the sole
legal government of China, and Taiwan, which established so-called
"diplomatic" ties with St. Lucia in 1983, is a part of the
People's Republic of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
