<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Maintains Impressive Housing Development Momentum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 30 (Xinhua) -- China will maintain large-scale
housing development and investment during the period of its Ninth
Five-Year Plan (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
Housing construction is expected to account for about four
percent of the country's total GNP during the period, according to
Minister of Construction Hou Jie.
</P>
<P>
During an interview with Xinhua, Hou said plans through 2010
call for the country to build a total of 1.2 billion sq.m. of
housing, with average annual housing construction of no less than
240 million sq.m.
</P>
<P>
He noted that each urban household will own an apartment with
average per-capita living space of 9 sq.m.. an some 70 percent of
the households will be able to afford well-equipped houses.
</P>
<P>
The fact that China has a population of 1.2 billion subject to
an annual net increase of 14 million raises strong demand for
housing, Hou said added.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party of China (CPC) and the Chinese government
have consistently paid close attention to the improvement of
housing conditions, and has introduced a series of reforms in this
regard.
</P>
<P>
Rapid growth in housing development and remarkable improvements
in the Chinese People's housing conditions have been reported over
the past five years. Annual urban housing construction has
surpassed 200 million sq.m., with the figure for rural housing
standing at 600 million sq.m.
</P>
<P>
As part of an effort to boost housing development and reform,
China has introduced commercialized housing, publicly funded
housing funds, individual home mortgage loans and a series of
other effective measures.
</P>
<P>
The 1.26 billion sq.m. of urban and rural housing China built
between 1992-1996 solved housing problems for approximately five
million households. Some 25 percent of urban households have been
moved into new housing in the past five years alone.
</P>
<P>
The country's average urban per-capita living space has grown
to 8.47 sq m,, with the figure for rural areas standing at 17.18
sq.m.
</P>
<P>
The "Comfortable Housing Project" has been implemented in more
than 200 cities, with the addition of over 20 million sq.m. of
housing space.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the rapid development of housing cooperatives has
effectively expanded fund-raising channels and has benefited the
low to medium income households.
</P>
<P>
Construction departments at various levels have extended great
effort to improve infrastructure facilities, including water
supply, drainage, heating, roads, bridges, highway, tree-planting
and environmental protection systems. Related efforts have greatly
helped to improve the people's living standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
