<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China International Quality Control Conference Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 30 (Xinhua) -- A three-day '97 International
Conference on Quality Control Circles (ICQCC'97) opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Quality control circles (QCC) are active in more than 70
countries and regions, and China, which introduced the idea in
1979, has built up more than 12 million of them in enterprises and
has improved efficiency of the economy for a savings of 196
billion yuan (23.7 billion US dollars) in the 19-year period.
</P>
<P>
The conference is expected to present papers on achievements of
the quality control circles, focusing on talent, quality, and
efficiency. It will also discuss the latest theories and the
orientation of quality studies, and the successes and experiences
of quality control both at home and abroad, and try to bring
quality control to a new stage of development.
</P>
<P>
The conference, the first of its kind in China, will be
attended by more than 1,300 delegates, 600 of whom from 20
countries and regions, according to a press conference held by the
China Quality Control Association Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
