<HEADLINE> World Bank Okays $50 Mln for Bosnia Herzegovina Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 29 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
announced the approval of totaling 50 million U.S. dollar credits
for emergency education and transport projects in Bosnia and
Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
The first credit of 11 million dollars is earmarked for Bosnia
Herzegovina second emergency education reconstruction interim
trust fund. The project will support reconstruction of about 18
primary schools in the Federation and about 7 primary schools in
the Republika Srpska. The financing also includes provision of
furniture and equipment for classrooms in these schools, provision
of textbooks and educational materials and technical assistance to
improve education finance and administration.
</P>
<P>
Another credit of some 39 million dollars equivalent is
provided for secondary emergency transport reconstruction project
interims trust fund.
</P>
<P>
The project consists of an adjustment component and a transport
investment component. The transport investment component will
carry out maintenance and reconstruction on the most critical
parts of the networks, supply equipment to restart transport
operations and ensure sustainability of reconstruction activities.
</P>
<P>
The credits will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessionary
lending arm. 
</P>
</TEXT>
