<HEADLINE> Clinton Calls Kennedy on His Decision not to Run </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 29 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton,
who has spent most of his vacation on Martha's Vineyard in
Massachusetts, took time out to call Massachusetts Representative
Joseph Kennedy II about the congressman's decision not to run for
governor next year.
</P>
<P>
White House spokesman Joe Lockhart said Friday the president
and first lady wanted Kennedy to know they were thinking about him
as he "made this difficult decision," The United Press
International reported.
</P>
<P>
Clinton reached Kennedy by telephone after the congressman
announced Thursday he would not seek the Massachusetts governor's
race.
</P>
<P>
Kennedy made the announcement in the wake of family
controversies that eroded what had been thought to be an
unbeatable popularity with voters. 
</P>
